## ğŸš€ How to Run

### Option 1: Open Locally
```bash
# Just open the file in any browser
open Netflix_Dashboard.html       # macOS
start Netflix_Dashboard.html      # Windows
xdg-open Netflix_Dashboard.html  # Linux
```

### Option 2: Deploy to GitHub Pages
1. Fork / clone this repository
2. Go to **Settings â†’ Pages**
3. Set source to `main` branch, root `/`
4. Your dashboard will be live at:
   `https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/Netflix_Dashboard.html`

---

## ğŸ” Key Insights

- **2020 was peak year** â€” 122 titles released, likely driven by COVID streaming surge
- **Content skews mature** â€” 50.4% of catalog is R/TV-MA rated
- **US dominates** but global content is strong â€” India, UK, Nigeria, Philippines all well represented
- **Drama is king** â€” 211 titles tagged as Dramas, often combined with Romance or International
- **Co-productions rising** â€” 22.7% of titles involve multiple countries
- **TV Shows underrepresented** â€” This snapshot is 96.8% movies, suggesting the dataset is movie-focused

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

- **Chart.js 4.4.1** â€” All 6 interactive charts
- **Pure HTML/CSS/JS** â€” Zero dependencies, zero build step
- **Google Fonts** â€” Bebas Neue + DM Sans
- **CSS Custom Properties** â€” Consistent theming
- **CSS Animations** â€” Smooth KPI counters and bar reveals

---

## ğŸ“ Dataset Columns

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `show_id` | Unique content identifier |
| `type` | Movie or TV Show |
| `title` | Content title |
| `director` | Director / cast (note: field contains mixed data) |
| `country` | Country of origin (comma-separated for co-productions) |
| `release_year` | Year of release |
| `rating` | Content rating (TV-MA, R, PG-13, etc.) |
| `duration` | Runtime in minutes (Movies) or seasons (TV) |
| `listed_in` | Genre tags (comma-separated, multi-genre) |

